                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2815: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 23, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>430. For Minister Johnson at Nanking: Your 983, November 22, 1 p.m. As yet the
                    Department has not been approached with such a request, but it approves the
                    sending of the Military Attaché to Chinchow for observation as proposed by you,
                    without reference to such a request and in regular course.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
